---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Nav from "../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="About MoveCostMatrix | Free Moving Cost Calculator" description="Learn about MoveCostMatrix — a free, privacy-first moving cost calculator that compares DIY truck, container, and professional mover estimates." canonical="/about">
  <script type="application/ld+json">
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      "itemListElement": [
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://movecostmatrix.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "https://movecostmatrix.com/about" }
      ]
    }
  </script>
  <Nav currentPath="/about" />

  <main>
  <section class="bg-canvas px-4 pb-28 pt-16 sm:pb-36 sm:pt-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      <span class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-wide text-mute">About</span>
      <h1 class="mt-2 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">About MoveCostMatrix</h1>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm leading-relaxed text-body content">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Our Mission</h2>
        <p>Moving is expensive, stressful, and often confusing. Most people only get an estimate from one type of mover. That is because comparing options is not easy. MoveCostMatrix fixes this. You can see the cost of every major moving method side by side. Instantly. No email required. No upsells.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Why We Built It</h2>
        <p>Many moving quote sites exist to sell your information to movers. Fill out one &ldquo;free quote&rdquo; form and your phone rings within minutes. We wanted something better. A calculator that respects your privacy as much as it respects the math. No data collection. No sales calls. No hidden agenda. Just a good-faith estimate to help you plan and negotiate with confidence.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">How It Works</h2>
        <p>Our calculator measures the distance between your origin and destination using the Haversine formula. It then adds a 20% road-adjustment factor for realism. For postal codes, we use the free zippopotam.us API to find coordinates. For city names, we use a fallback algorithm. The result feeds into three pricing models based on industry data from the American Moving and Storage Association and published rate schedules:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
          <li><strong>DIY Truck Rental</strong> — $0.80 per mile, plus base fees typical of U-Haul and similar providers</li>
          <li><strong>Moving Containers</strong> — $1.50 per mile, based on PODS and 1-800-PACK-RAT pricing</li>
          <li><strong>Professional Movers</strong> — $2.50 per mile, from industry averages across United Van Lines, Atlas Van Lines, and Mayflower</li>
        </ul>
        <p>All results are in USD and can be shown in 7 currencies. A slider lets you adjust the distance and see how small changes affect your total.</p>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Design Principles</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
          <li><strong>Privacy-first by default.</strong> Everything runs in your browser. No accounts, no registration, no tracking of your inputs. We only use anonymized analytics to measure traffic.</li>
          <li><strong>No email gate.</strong> See your estimate right away — no email address needed.</li>
          <li><strong>Unbiased comparison.</strong> We show all three options every time. No mover pays us to promote their service.</li>
          <li><strong>Accessible.</strong> Dark mode, keyboard navigation, high-contrast text, and responsive design for all devices.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>MoveCostMatrix provides estimates for planning only. We are not a moving broker, moving company, or financial advisor. Always get binding quotes from licensed moving companies before you commit. The rates in our calculator are based on national averages and may not match your specific situation.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
  </main>

  <Footer currentPath="/about" />
</Layout>
